NT|^B@2|cp|8|at|
hondo717: |cp||at|When leading back partner's suit as in trick two, you lead back "remaining count."  So, after winning the first club, pam would lead back high club if she had a doubleton left (e.g. she started with 3), and low with 3 left. Therefore, the 5 of clubs is the correct lead back.  That helps ira figure out how many clubs ally has.  ally, also made a slight error on the 2nd club trick. She should win with the K, not the Q.  When you play the Q and it wins, pam and ira now know you have the K, whereas if you play the K, the location of the Q is still a mystery.|
