hondo717: |cp||at|OK. This hand illustrated some good bidding principles regarding competing after a weak NT. Since they were playing Brozel, which I will briefly explain in a minute, pam's 2@S bid was fine, showing spades and a minor. Unlike with the strong NT, where I suggest systems on/stolen bid doubles, I suggest you play Lebensohl as partner of the weak NT bidder. So, if there is an interference Lebensohl when playing weak NT and systems on/stolen bid if playing strong NT.|
